      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're not using a multimeter, a clicking sound right before the humming could indicate that the capacitor is struggling to start the fan, which is a common symptom of a failing capacitor. A dead motor might not make a clicking sound, but it could fail silently or produce a grinding noise. A weird smell could be a sign of overheating and potential capacitor failure as well. If you notice a burning smell, turn off the unit immediately. It's always safer to err on the side of caution and contact a professional, especially if you're unsure of the issue.",
